# grapher_smoke.numos — open the Grapher app, screenshot, and ASSERT it is active.
#
# Phase 8G smoke test. GrapherApp is LVGL-native but, unlike the Phase 5A-7C apps,
# it depends on the legacy RPN numeric pipeline (Tokenizer/Parser/Evaluator/
# VariableContext) through its GraphModel. Phase 8G native-ports that minimal
# prerequisite (Arduino String shim charAt/equalsIgnoreCase; VariableContext NVS
# guarded #ifdef ARDUINO; PSRAMBuffer std::malloc fallback; esp_heap_caps/yield
# guarded in GrapherApp.cpp) and wires Grapher into the emulator build filter and
# NativeHal routing (launchApp id 1, aliases grapher/graph).
#
# This script opens Grapher through the emulator-only `open_app` command (Phase 5A:
# it calls the SAME NativeHal launchApp() the launcher uses — id 1, the Grapher card
# id, so it is deterministic and does not depend on fragile grid navigation),
# captures a screenshot, and asserts the active app is "Grapher".
#
# SCOPE: this is an INITIAL-STATE smoke ONLY. Grapher opens on its "Expressions" tab
# with focus at the tab bar and ZERO functions (GrapherApp.cpp begin() -> Tab::
# EXPRESSIONS, Focus::TAB_BAR, _numFuncs=0). The script does NOT enter a function,
# switch to the Graph/Table tab, trace, pan, or zoom — none of the plotting/sampling/
# yield paths run on first open. The Graph (Kandinsky/PSRAM) panel is created lazily
# only on the first Graph-tab switch, which this script never triggers.
#
# This phase makes NO golden claim; the screenshot is a CANDIDATE for human review
# only (a future golden would mask the StatusBar clock, like the other app smokes).
#
# Timing notes (deterministic, step-ms 16):
#   * 200 frames -> splash (~frame 125) is done; we are in the launcher.
#   * 60 frames  -> Grapher screen load + 200ms fade settles after open_app.
#
# Run:
#   program --headless --deterministic --script tests/emulator/scripts/grapher_smoke.numos \
#           --frames 800 --screenshot out/grapher_smoke.ppm --quiet
# Exit codes: 0 ok · 2 script/parse error · 3 screenshot write error · 4 assertion failure.

log "grapher_smoke: waiting for launcher"
wait 200

# Open Grapher (emulator launchApp id 1 — same id as the launcher's Grapher card).
open_app Grapher
wait 60

# Screenshot FIRST: the deferred capture happens on this frame, before the assert
# runs on a later frame, so the artifact is produced even if the assertion fails.
screenshot out/grapher_smoke.ppm
log "grapher_smoke: screenshot captured"

assert_app Grapher
log "grapher_smoke: assertion passed (Grapher active)"
